newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: Rugby union-ACT humiliate New South Wales.
newsitem.headline: Rugby union-ACT humiliate New South Wales.

text.p: Australian Capital Territory moved one point clear at the top of the Super 12 standings on Saturday after humiliating New South Wales 56-9 with a stunning display of attacking rugby.
But the Brumbies' lead in the Super 12 standings was brief, as defending champions Auckland leadfrogged them into top spot after their defeat of Natal on Sunday.

ACT are set to be overtaken by either Auckland or Natal who meet at Eden Park on Sunday, but thrilled a record crowd at Bruce Stadium by scoring eight tries to nil against their wealthier compatriots.
